  m_Name: Lumbar_Vertebrae_L7
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Lumbar_Vertebrae_L7
  partName: Lumbar Vertebrae L7
  descriptionChunks:
  - The lumbar vertebra L7 is the final lumbar vertebra in the canine vertebral column
    and serves as an important transitional structure between the lumbar spine and
    sacrum. It supports substantial body weight while allowing controlled spinal
    flexibility during locomotion and posture changes.
  - This vertebra provides attachment sites for muscles and ligaments involved in
    stabilizing the lower back and hindlimbs. The region surrounding L7 contains
    important spinal nerves contributing to pelvic limb movement and sensory function.
